  "texts": [
    "For computational efficiency, we ran Bowtie 2 with its default behaviour to align every read at most once.",
    "We then analysed the orientation of paired-end reads (Fig. 2b).",
    "During assembly, circular sequences are broken by an artificial breakpoint to represent them as linear contigs.",
    "Consequently, DNA sequencing that occurred across this breakpoint will produce paired-end reads that align in a reverse-forward orientation to the ends of the contig.",
    "In contrast, if a sequence is not circular, then all paired-end reads are expected to align in a forward-reverse orientation."
  ],
